During data analysis, neutral logarithmic transformation is a common method for manipulating the outlying data from a positively skewed distribution to one that is closer to the bulk of the data to allow the variable to be normally distributed [13]. In this study, using a model in which the outcome variable has been log-transformed and the predictors have not, it is natural to interpret the exponential function of the ANCOVA coefficients. In terms of (simplified) equations, the model with log-transformed outcome variable is \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
